SCHEMAS CLOSE
ECHO === DotTalk++ command sweep (non-exit, non-UI, non-shell, non-clear) ===
VERSION
HELP
FOXHELP
COMMANDSHELP
PREDHELP
PREDICATES
SQLVER

ECHO === open a known table (adjust name if your dataset differs) ===
USE TEACHERS NOINDEX
AREA
STATUS
FIELDS
STRUCT
RECNO
TOP
RECNO
SKIP 1
RECNO
BOTTOM
RECNO
GO 1
GOTO 1
DISPLAY 1
RECORD 1
LIST 3
COUNT

INDEX ON LNAME TO TEACHERS
SET INDEX TO TEACHERS
TUP

TOP
LOCATE FOR .T.

SCAN FOR .T.
ENDSCAN


SELE
SCAN FOR LNAME = WHITE
   TUP
ENDSCAN

ECHO === expression/string utilities (safe) ===
ECHO TRIM('  a  ')
ECHO ALLTRIM('  a  ')
ECHO LTRIM('  a  ')
ECHO RTRIM('  a  ')
ECHO UPPER('abc')
ECHO LOWER('ABC')
ECHO LEFT('ABCDE',2)
ECHO RIGHT('ABCDE',2)
ECHO SUBSTR('ABCDE',2,3)
ECHO LEN('ABCDE')
ECHO AT('BC','ABCDE')
ECHO ATC('bc','ABCDE')
ECHO CHR(65)
ECHO SPACE(3)
ECHO REPLICATE('x',5)
ECHO STUFF('ABCDE',2,2,'ZZ')
ECHO PADL('A',5)
ECHO PADR('A',5)
ECHO PADC('A',5)
ECHO STR(12.34,8,2)
ECHO VAL('123')
ECHO EVAL('1+2')
ECHO PROPER('john smith')
ECHO TRANSFORM(123.45)
ECHO ASC('A')
ECHO ASCEND('A')
ECHO DESCEND('A')
ECHO BOOLEAN('T')
ECHO LIKE('ABC' LIKE 'A%')
ECHO NORMALIZE('  "abc"  ')
ECHO FORMULA('1+2')

ECHO === indexing/order/relations/schema (invoke HELP/FOXHELP to avoid side effects here) ===
FOXHELP INDEX
FOXHELP SETINDEX
FOXHELP SETORDER
FOXHELP SET UNIQUE
FOXHELP REINDEX
FOXHELP CNX
FOXHELP SETCNX
FOXHELP SETFILTER
FOXHELP SET RELATION
FOXHELP REL
FOXHELP REL_LIST
FOXHELP REL_REFRESH
FOXHELP SCHEMA
FOXHELP SCHEMAS
FOXHELP VALIDATE

ECHO === editing/lifecycle (invoke HELP/FOXHELP to avoid modifying data in this sweep) ===
FOXHELP APPEND
FOXHELP APPEND_BLANK
FOXHELP REPLACE
FOXHELP MULTIREP
FOXHELP CALC
FOXHELP CALCWRITE
FOXHELP DELETE
FOXHELP RECALL
FOXHELP UNDELETE
FOXHELP PACK
FOXHELP ZAP
FOXHELP LOCK
FOXHELP UNLOCK
FOXHELP EDIT

ECHO === import/export/sqlite integration (invoke HELP/FOXHELP to avoid file/db side effects) ===
FOXHELP EXPORT
FOXHELP IMPORT
FOXHELP SQL
FOXHELP SQLSEL
FOXHELP SQLITE
FOXHELP INSERT
FOXHELP UPDATE
FOXHELP WHERE

ECHO === scripting/loops (invoke HELP; running nested control blocks depends on your harness rules) ===
FOXHELP DOTSCRIPT
FOXHELP TEST
FOXHELP LOOP
FOXHELP ENDLOOP
FOXHELP LOOP_BUFFER
FOXHELP SCAN_BUFFER
FOXHELP WHILE
FOXHELP ENDWHILE
FOXHELP UNTIL
FOXHELP ENDUNTIL
FOXHELP CONTINUE

ECHO === UI/tvision/shell/clear/quit are intentionally not invoked in this sweep ===
FOXHELP FOXTALK
FOXHELP FOXPRO
FOXHELP BROWSE
FOXHELP BROWSER
FOXHELP BROWSETUI
FOXHELP BROWSETV
FOXHELP SUPERBROWSER
FOXHELP SB
FOXHELP SBR
FOXHELP TVISION
FOXHELP COLOR
FOXHELP !
FOXHELP BANG
FOXHELP RUN
FOXHELP CLEAR
HELP QUIT

ECHO === close out ===
CLOSE
ECHO === sweep complete ===
